            {
              "id": "CVE-2025-24970",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "io.netty:netty-handler: SslHandler doesn't correctly validate packets which can lead to native crash when using native SSLEngine"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Netty, an asynchronous, event-driven network application framework, has a vulnerability starting in version 4.1.91.Final and prior to version 4.1.118.Final. When a special crafted packet is received via SslHandler it doesn't correctly handle validation of such a packet in all cases which can lead to a native crash. Version 4.1.118.Final contains a patch. As workaround its possible to either disable the usage of the native SSLEngine or change the code manually."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-24970",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2025-24970\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: io.netty:netty-handler\nFixed Version: 4.1.118.Final\nLink: [CVE-2025-24970](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-24970)\nNetty, an asynchronous, event-driven network application framework, has a vulnerability starting in version 4.1.91.Final and prior to version 4.1.118.Final. When a special crafted packet is received via SslHandler it doesn't correctly handle validation of such a packet in all cases which can lead to a native crash. Version 4.1.118.Final contains a patch. As workaround its possible to either disable the usage of the native SSLEngine or change the code manually.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2025-24970**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|io.netty:netty-handler|4.1.118.Final|[CVE-2025-24970](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-24970)|\n\nNetty, an asynchronous, event-driven network application framework, has a vulnerability starting in version 4.1.91.Final and prior to version 4.1.118.Final. When a special crafted packet is received via SslHandler it doesn't correctly handle validation of such a packet in all cases which can lead to a native crash. Version 4.1.118.Final contains a patch. As workaround its possible to either disable the usage of the native SSLEngine or change the code manually."
